From e335f5e36abdc7beef15276948e5bc901982f969 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 06:05:34 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 22/23] UI rebuild stage 1: unify rail + drawer on a 6-job
 model

Add src/workspaceJobs.js as the single source of truth for back-end nav:
six job doors (READ/MARRY/KEYS/FLASH/LIVE/REFERENCE), each with a primary
tab and member modes. Every one of the 49 workspace tabs maps to exactly
one job (verified 1:1, zero orphans), with a REFERENCE fallback so no tab
can become unreachable.

CommandShell now derives BOTH the rail (was 8 arbitrary tabs, 2 vocab) and
the drawer sections from JOBS, so one job wears one name everywhere. Rail
doors stay lit while on any member tab (BCM keeps READ highlighted).
